description:
New readers start here! Jump on board with one of comics creative powerhouses Prog 1925 sees the second episodes in the brand-new line-up of stunning stories with everything from future cops to ancient barbarian warriors, mutant bounty hunters to rogue assassins! Wrapped in a brand new cover by the legendary Brian Bolland, Prog 1924 includes FIVE brand new stories, plus primer pages for each strip so you can launch straight into some of our biggest characters! Dredd experiences the repercussions of the Titan penal revolt in Enceladus: New Life by Rob Williams and Henry Flint; Strontium Dog Johnny Alpha is given a mission to undertake if he's to save his friends from execution in Strontium Dog: The Stix Fix Job by John Wagner and Carlos Ezquerra; Celtic barbarian Sline battles against the Drune Lords in the second book of The Brutania Chronicles, Primordial, by Pat Mills and Simon Davis; the Russian assassin Orlok finds a new mission in The Rasputin Caper by Arthur Wyatt and Jake Lynch; and things arent quite as they seem in Grey Area: Another Day On The Job by Dan Abnett and Mark Harrison.

Cover: Brian Bolland

  • Judge Dredd - Enceladus New Life (Part One) (Rob Williams - Henry Flint)
  • Sline: The Brutania Chronicles Book Two - Primordial (Part One) (Pat Mills - Simon Davis)
  • Grey Area - Another Day On the Job (Part One) (Dan Abnett - Mark Harrison)
  • Orlok, Agent of East-Meg One - The Rasputin Caper (Part One) (Arthur Wyatt - Jake Lynch)
  • Stronium Dog - The Stix Fix (Part One) (John Wagner - Carlos Ezquerra)
name: Prog 1924

description: Scorpion squares off against Sub-Zero in the epic fight you've been waiting for! Meanwhile, the Shokan army makes their move on Kotal Kahn!
name: Blood Gods Chapter 14:  City of Ice and Hellfire

description: It's everyone's favorite furious fowl as you've never seen them before! New Yolk City is your typical bustling metropolis and like every big city it has a dark side. Through lies, deceit and corruption, King Pig and his henchmen have taken over the town and have made life miserable for its citizens. This makes one group of birds angry...Super Angry! This new group of would-be heroes, with powers beyond mortal birds, fight a covert war against King Pig and his minions. They are the Super Angry Birds!
name: The Eagle's Eye

description: You though they were Angry Birds before but wait till you see the Super Angry Birds! When King Pig begins a counterfeiting ring to bring all the riches of New Yolk City to his feet, it's up to the Super Angry Birds to spoil his plans and leave him with nothing but rotten eggs!
name: The Nest Egg

description: High school student Kei Nagai is killed in a traffic accident, but immediately revives to learn that he may not be human at all. Instead, he may be a Demi-Human, a mysterious almost immortal being blessed with amazing super-human abilities. Scared, he runs away, and is aided in his escape from society by his friend Kai. Unfortunately for Kei, the manhunt is on and he will soon be caught within a conflict between mankind and other Demi-Humans as they prepare to fight for global supremacy.
name: Vol. 4

description: Twelve thousand years after Genesis of Aquarion on the planet Vega, Amata Sora meets Mikono Suzushiro. Together, part of the organization Neo-DEAVA, they must defend their planet from relentless invaders attacking from Altair, a sister planet devoid of females. These two unexpected heroes, along with other young men and women, known as Elements, pilot massive robots called Aquaria, in defense of their planet, in a battle against malicious assailants trying to abduct woman from their home planet.
name: Vol. 1

description: Tired of accusations that family connections got him his current position, Ritsu Onodera quits his job as an editor at his father's company and transfers to Marukawa Publishing. Once there, he is assigned to the shojo manga editorial departmentsomething he has no interest in and no experience with! Having sworn he'd never fall in love again, the last thing he wants to do is work on love stories. To make matters worse, it turns out that his overbearing boss, Masamune Takano, is actually his first love from high school!
name: The Case of Ritsu Onodera

description: At the request of Barabas, Suske cultivates an age-old seed to a beautiful flower with delicious looking fruits. Wiske is jealous at the attention Suske gives to the flower. The flower can speak however, and promises Wiske the unrequitted love of Suske, if he eats from his fruit. But when Suske takes a bite, he transforms into a golden finch and a race against the clock begins.
name: Suskewiet

description: The battle between good and evil breaks loose in J.Rom2. And evil gets a face: Abaddon! J.Rom takes on his archnemesis in an epic fight hunderd meters above the ground. In the meantime Pi and Birdsong have the sinister Dr. Yulls against them when he raids their headquarters. Is Force standing its ground?
name: Helder
